-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                     Astral3D installation instructions
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1.) Supported UNIX Platforms
2.) Requirements
3.) Setting up the Installation
4.) Installation
5.) Usage

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. SUPPORTED UNIX PLATFORMS

Currently is supported only Linux platform.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. REQUIREMENTS

Astral3D needs these development libraries: OpenGL
                                            OpenGL Utilities (GLU)
                                            SDL
                                            SDL_Image

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. SETTING UP THE INSTALLATION

Before the installation you have to specify directories where header files and
library files of libraries above are located. Usually you allready have
OpenGL and SDL libraries installed with your distribution. Therefore there
can be problems with finding some libraries outside default path dir settings.

For example: You have installed SDL_Image library to your home directory.
             You propably need run this:

                export CPPFLAGS="$CPPFLAGS -I$HOME/include/SDL/"
                export LDFLAGS="$LDFLAGS -L$HOME/lib/"

             before running configure script.

Notice that although you have OpenGL libary installed in your system you
sometime need specify its library path:

                export LDFLAGS="$LDFLAGS -L/usr/X11R6/lib/"

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. INSTALLATION

You can run root or user installation. If you run root installation
the library (libastral3d.a) in installed to /usr/local/lib and header files
are copied to /usr/local/include. If you run user installation the
libary is installed to the lib directory in the path given by --prefix
argument of the configure script. Header files are copied to the
include directory also in the path given by the --prefix argument.

root installation:

    ./configure
    make
    su -c "make install"

non root installation (user installation):

    ./configure --prefix=$HOME
    make
    make install

Run ./configure --help for more info.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5. USAGE

This section describes how to use Astral3D in your projects.

    How to compile 'example.cpp' using Astral3D:

 -> root installation, SDL_image in the system:
    g++ -o example example.cpp -L/usr/X11R6/lib -lGL -lGLU -lm `sdl-config --cflags --libs` -lSDL_image -lastral3d

 -> user installation, SDL_image in the system:
    g++ -o example example.cpp -I$HOME/include -L$HOME/lib -L/usr/X11R6/lib -lGL -lGLU -lm `sdl-config --cflags --libs` -lSDL_image -lastral3d

 -> user installation, SDL_image in the home directory:
    g++ -o example example.cpp -I$HOME/include/SDL -I$HOME/include -L$HOME/lib -L/usr/X11R6/lib -lGL -lGLU -lm `sdl-config --cflags --libs` -lSDL_image -lastral3d
